<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Csv converter</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon" />
    <link href="/fontAwesome/fontawesome-free-5.13.0-web/css/all.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
        content="default-src *; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@2.9.3/dist/Chart.min.js">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@2.9.3/dist/Chart.min.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="navbar">
        <div class="home">
            <div class="link_right">
                <a href="#">
                    <i class="fas fa-home">
                    </i>
                </a>
                <div class="home1">
                    <h3>Home</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rightnavbar">
            <div class="link_right">
                <a href="https://github.com/Rogerpeke97" target="_blank">
                    <i class="fab fa-github"></i>
                </a>
                <div class="github">
                    <h3>Github</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="link_right">
                <a href="#" target="_blank">
                    <i class="fab fa-linkedin-in"></i>
                </a>
                <div class="github">
                    <h3>LinkedIn</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="link_right">
                <form action="/log_out" enctype="multipart/form-data" method="POST">
                <button target="_blank" type="submit" id="login_form">
                    <i class='fas fa-sign-out-alt'></i>
                </button>
                </form>
                <div class="github">
                    <% if (user) { %>
                        <h3  id="username"><%= user.name %></h3>
                        <% } %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container" id="container">
        <div class="grid1">
            <div class="logo">
                <div class="logoimg"><img src="/LogoMakr_8xcq1g.png" alt=""></div>
                <div class="explainercsv">
                    <h1>Csv data visualization using chartjs!</h1>
                </div>
                <div class="buttons">
                    <i class="fas fa-file-excel"></i>
                    <i class="fas fa-file-csv"></i>
                    <i class="far fa-file-alt"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="arrow">
                    <a href="#middle" class="fa fa-chevron-down"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid2" id="middle">
            <div class="vertical">
                <div class="image_example"></div>
                <h2>
                    The vertical chart is a chart with rectangular bars with lengths proportional to the values that
                    they represent. One axis of the chart shows the specific categories being compared, and the other
                    axis represent different values that are modified according to the data being uploaded.
                    It provides a visual presentation of categorical data. Categorical data is a grouping of data into
                    discrete groups, such as months of the year, age group, shoe sizes, and animals. These categories
                    are usually qualitative.
                </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="multiaxis">
                <div class="imagemulti_example"></div>
                <h2>
                    The multi-axial chart is a line chart, as the name suggests, it's line chart can be
                    configured for multiple axes. It is a special type of chart that allows multiple y-axes to be
                    rendered in the same chart.
                </h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid3">
            <form action="/uploadedfile" enctype="multipart/form-data" method="POST" id="form">
                <div class="numerodos">
                    <div class="loadingfile">
                        <div class="browsefiles">
                            <label for="fileUp" class="btn">Browse Files</label>
                            <input id="fileUp" type="file" name="myFile" style="display: none;" />
                        </div>
                        <h1 id="aboutToUpload">File selected:

                        </h1>
                        <div class="uploadclick">
                            <label for="uploadClick" class="btn">
                                <h2>Upload!</h2>
                            </label>
                            <input id="uploadClick" type="submit" formtarget="_blank" style="display: none;" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="csvimage">
                        <i class="fas fa-file-csv"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="numerotres">

                </div>
            </form>
        </div>
        <div class="grid4" id="grid4">
            <div class="graphconfig">
                <div class="row1">
                    <h2>Chart type</h2>
                    <h3 id="multiaxial">Multi-axial</h3>
                    <h3 id="vertical">Vertical</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="row2">
                    <h2>Chart title</h2>
                    <input type="text" id="chart_title" value="Write your chart title here!" autocomplete="off" />
                    <h3 id="upload_chart_title">Apply</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="row3">
                    <div class="removerows">
                        <h2>Saved Files</h2>
                        <i class="fa fa-question-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h4>No Files Found</h4>
                    <button type="submit">Apply</button>
                </div>
                <div class="row4">
                    <h2>Show all content</h2>
                    <h3 id="view_all">View full chart</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="myChart" id="chartContainer">
                <canvas id="myChart"></canvas>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid5">
            <div class="column1">
                <div class="explain_image">

                </div>
                <div class="explain_text">
                    <h3>What this converter does at default is remove the first row of the csv or the first line
                        break and calculate the mean of the different numbers separated by commas in the different rows.
                        While calculating the mean of these numbers the first variable in the array is removed since
                        it's the variant that will be the x axis in the chart. The colors, given the amount of
                        numbers in each x variable, are randomized. Hence, if you update the chart or reload the website
                        all the values colors will change.
                    </h3>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column2">
                <div class="explain_image">

                </div>
                <div class="explain_text">
                    <h3>When view full chart is selected no rows will be deleted (Except the first line[0], which in the
                        example csv file says 'Year'), the mean of each line break will not be calculated and each row
                        will be displayed from top to bottom with it's corresponding values.
                    </h3>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="logged.js"></script>
</body>

</html>